<h2> Privacy Policy </h2>

<p>
This Policy applies to all MicroPython websites accessed under the
micropython.org domain name.  These sites are administered by George Robotics
Ltd (UK) and George Robotics Pty Ltd (AU).
</p>

<h3> 1. Personal information that is collect and processed </h3>

<p>
In order to operate and do business there is certain personal information that
we collect, process and store:

<ol style='list-style-type: lower-alpha'>

<li>
Web browsing &ndash;
When you browse any of our websites we automatically receive your computer's
internet protocol (IP) address.  We make this address anonymous so it cannot be
traced back to you, and store it in our web server logs for debugging and
analytics purposes.  We do not use any third-party service for analytics.
</li>

<li>
Newsletter &ndash;
If you explicitly sign-up to receive our newsletter we will collect your
email address.  We may use this email address to send you newsletter emails
including information about new products, offers and other updates regarding
MicroPython related software and hardware.  You can unsubscribe from the
newsletter at anytime.  Your email address is never shared with a third
party.
</li>

<li>
Store purchases &ndash;
When you purchase something from our store (found at
<a href="https://store.micropython.org">store.micropython.org</a>) we collect
the personal information that you explicitly give us such as your name, email
address and shipping address.  This information is used to send you email
confirmations and notifications about your purchase, as well as to ship you
your order.  The information is retained offline for seven years for accounting
purposes.
</li>

</ol>
</p>

<h3> 2. Legal basis for collection and processing </h3>

<p>
Our legal basis for processing your data in order to send your our newsletter
is that you have consented to our doing so by explicitly providing your
email address and then responding to the email confirmation.
</p>

<p>
Our legal basis for processing your personal details for an order is that you
have consented by explicitly making a purchase, and the processing is in our
legitimate interest to enable us to sell our products to you.
</p>

<h3> 3. Third party data processors </h3>

<p>
All our website financial transactions are handled through our payment services
provider, <a href="https://stripe.com">Stripe</a>.  When making a purchase in
our store you will need to provide certain information directly to Stripe.  We
share your email address with Stripe just before you make a payment so they can
identify you.  We do not collect any credit card information from you.
</p>

<p>
Our shipping partners are <a href="http://esg-workstation.com/">ESG Workstation (DE)</a>
and they are responsible for shipping your order to you.  In order to ship your
order we must share your name, email and shipping address with them.
</p>

<h3> 4. Cookies </h3>

<p>
A cookie consists of information sent by a web server (us) to a web browser
(you), and stored by the browser. The information is then sent back to the
server (from you to us) each time the browser requests a page from the server.
This enables the web server to identify and track the web browser.
</p>

<p>
We use "session" cookies only on the store website.  They are integral to
providing the online shopping service: the session cookies keep track of you
whilst you navigate the store to remember what is in your cart.
</p>

<p>
If you do not want to use cookies then you are unable to make purchases on
the store website.  Instead, send us an email with your order.
</p>

<h3> 5. Disclosure </h3>

<p>
We may disclose information about you:

<ol style='list-style-type: lower-alpha'>
<li> to the extent that we are required to do so by law; </li>

<li> in connection with any legal proceedings or prospective legal proceedings; </li>

<li> to establish, exercise or defend our legal right; and </li>

<li> to the purchaser (or prospective purchaser) of any business or asset which
we are (or are contemplating) selling. </li>
</ol>
</p>

<p>
Except as provided in this Privacy Policy, we will not provide your
information to third parties.
</p>

<h3> 6. Security of data </h3>

<p>
We will take reasonable technical and organisational precautions to prevent
the loss or misuse of personal information.  We will store all personal
information you provide on our secure servers.
</p>

<h3> 7. Policy amendments </h3>

<p>
We may update this policy from time-to-time by posting a new version on our
website.
</p>

<h3> 8. Third party websites </h3>

<p>
The website contains links to other websites.  We are not responsible for the
privacy policies or practices of third party websites.
</p>

<h3> 9. Your rights </h3>

<p>
At any time you may ask us to provide you with the personal information we hold
about you.  At any time you may ask us to update any of your personal
information, or ask to withdraw your consent for us to hold and use your
personal information for marketing purposes.  We will respond to your request
as soon as it is practical to do so.
</p>

<p>
If you would like to request information or make changes, or have questions about
this Privacy Policy, please contact us via email using
<img src="/static/home/img/emx1.png" style="height:16px; vertical-align:-3px">
-at-
<img src="/static/home/img/emx2.png" style="height:16px; vertical-align:-3px">.
</p>

The Information Commissioner's Office is the UK's independent body set up to
uphold information rights.  For more information see
<a href="https://ico.org.uk/">ico.org.uk</a>.


